# Match-3 Puzzle — Project Configuration

## Project Overview
- **Unity Version:** 2022.3 LTS
- **Render Pipeline:** URP (2D Renderer)
- **Genre:** Match-3 puzzle
- **Target Platform:** PC (Steam) + Console (PS5 / Xbox)
- **Target FPS:** 60 (smooth tile animations)

## Architecture

### Assembly Structure
```
MyGame.Core         — events, pooling, utilities
MyGame.Board        — grid, tiles, matching, cascade, special tiles
MyGame.Gameplay     — levels, objectives, scoring, combos, boosters
MyGame.Meta         — lives, energy, currencies, progression, shop
MyGame.UI           — HUD, level select, shop, popups
MyGame.Systems      — audio, save, store/DLC, analytics
MyGame.Editor       — level editor tools
```

### Key Systems
- **Board System** — NxM grid, tile types, swap detection, match-3+ logic
- **Cascade System** — gravity, refill, chain combo detection
- **Special Tiles** — striped (row/col clear), wrapped (3x3), color bomb (all of one type)
- **Level Objectives** — score target, clear blockers, collect items, reach bottom
- **Lives System** — 5 lives, 30-min regen, spend soft currency for an extra life
- **Progression** — 100+ levels, level packs, star ratings (1-3)
- **Booster System** — pre-game and in-game boosters (purchasable)

### Scene Structure
- `S_Bootstrap` — persistent services (save, audio, store/DLC)
- `S_Meta` — map/level select screen
- `S_Game` — gameplay board (level config loaded as data)

## Skills to Load
- `match3` — grid system, matching, cascades, special tiles
- `object-pooling` — pool all tiles and effects
- `state-machine` — game states, board states
- `save-system` — level progress, stars, currencies
- `audio` — tile pop sounds, combo chains
- `ui-toolkit` — level select grid, shop UI
- `dotween` — smooth tile animations

## Rules
Follow all rules in `.claude/rules/`. Platform guidance — PC/console performance budgets, input and
display handling — comes from `.claude/rules/pc-console.md`, which is always in force; there is no
platform skill to load.

## Key Conventions
- **All tile operations are grid-based** — visual position lerps to grid position
- **Pool all tiles** — never Instantiate/Destroy during gameplay
- **Cascade loop** — match → destroy → gravity → refill → re-check (repeat until stable)
- **Mouse and gamepad input** — mouse drags a tile to an adjacent cell; gamepad moves a board cursor
  and confirms. Both snap to H/V direction
- **Animations via DOTween** — tile movement, scaling, color transitions
- **Level data as JSON** — board layout, objectives, available tile types per level
- **Star rating** — moves taken vs par moves
- **Aspect ratios** — board and UI anchor for 16:9 through ultrawide (21:9)

## Input Map
```
Player:
  Move Cursor — Mouse position / Left Stick or D-pad
  Select Tile — Left Mouse on tile / A button on cursor
  Swap — Drag to adjacent tile (H/V only) / D-pad direction while held
  Use Booster — Click booster button, then click target tile
```
Every binding is rebindable, and UI prompts follow the active device (see `.claude/rules/pc-console.md`).

## MCP Integration
Unity MCP at `http://localhost:8080/mcp`. Use for UI screen building and board setup.
